info.name: UXCAM DATA ACCESS V2 APIs Documentation

item.name: Overview
Rate Limiting
item.description:
**Status Code: 429**

This means that a customer made frequent calls to an API that exceeded the call **rate limit**. Currently, we have implemented the following rate limit.

1. A maximum of 10 concurrent requests per second
    
2. A maximum of 1000 requests per hour
    
3. A Total number of 500 records can be fetched on a single request
    

If any of the above-mentioned conditions are met regarding the rate limit, then APIs will start to throw a 429 status code. This limit will only be reset every hour.

_**Note: To minimize rate-limiting errors, consider combining multiple filters, groupings, and aggregations into a single request to make multiple queries.**_

response.name: Analyze Events

item.description:
To use the UXCam Data Access APIs, you will need to have two authentication parameters: API Key and App ID (which is the ID of the app you created on the UXCam Dashboard).

These parameters can be obtained by following the instructions below.

- Go to App Settings
- Browse into the Application tab.
- Click on the Data Access API tab. (Here, you will get the App ID and API key)
- If the API key already exists, **use it**, else you might have to **create one**. To create one, click on the "Generate random API key" button.
    

The identity of each application is unique and is represented by the App ID. It is automatically generated once, and can not be changed. An API key is a unique identifier used to connect or authenticate an API call. These authentication parameters can be included either in the request header or in the request URL itself.

| **App ID** | **60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb** |
| --- | --- |
| **API Key** | **9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618** |

item.description:
This pagination parameter divides a large data set into smaller sections to facilitate the handling of JSON responses. This parameter supports **integer** values only.

**page(Default Value=1)**: a page refers to a portion of the data set that is returned in response to the API request. Typically, The API request will retrieve one page of data, and additional pages can be accessed by specifying a different "page number" in subsequent API requests.

**page_size(Default Value=50 and max value = 500)**:  Page size defines the size of pages that are used to limit the total number of records in the APIs response.

_**Note: If the pagination parameters are not passed then the APIs response returned the first page with a total number of 50 records on the page.**_

  
  

```
page=1&page_size=20

```

response.name: Operator Name: greater_or_equal
Operator Name: less_or_equal

item.description:
Filter parameter is used to narrow down the results by a combination of filter attribute name, filter operator, and filter value. They are applied as a list of dictionaries, where each dictionary represents a separate filter. Each individual filter contains three keys: **attribute**, **operator**, and **value** in the dictionary.

```
Single filter sample:
filters=[{"attribute":"Attribute Name","operator":"Operator Name","value":"Filter value"}]
Multiple filter sample :
filters=[{"attribute":"Attribute Name","operator":"Operator Name","value":"Filter value"},{"attribute":"Attribute Name","operator":"Operator Name","value":"Filter value"}]

```

#### Filters Operators

##### Integer Filter Operators

These operators can only be used with filter attributes that are of type **integer** or **float**.

| **Operator Name** | **Operator Meaning** | **Operator Data Value Type** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| greater | \> | Integer |
| less | < | Integer |
| greater_or_equal | \>= | Integer |
| less_or_equal | <= | Integer |

##### String Filter Operators

These operators can only be used with filter attributes that are of type **string**.

| **Operator Name** | **Operator Meaning** | **Operator Data Value Type** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| equal | \= | String |
| not_equal | != | String |
| in | ∈ | List/Array of string |
| not_in | ∉ | List/Array of string |
| contains | Contain substring | String |
| not_contains | Does not Contain substring | String |

##### List Filter Operators

These operators can only be used with filter attributes that are of type **list of strings**. The only attribute utilized in list operators is **session_screen_list**.

| Operator Name | Operator Symbol | Operator Data Value Type |
| --- | --- | --- |
| has_any | ∈ | List/Array of string |
| not_has_any | ∉ | List/Array of string |

##### DateTime Filter Operators

These operators can only be used with filter attributes that are of type **DateTime**. By default, the response will display data from the last 30 days.

_**Note: Uxcam Data Access APIs support ISO-8601 format (zulu format)**_

_**Example: 2023-01-01, 2023-01-01T11:23:12Z**_

| **Operator Name** | **Operator Symbol** | **Operator Data Value Type** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| on | \= | DateTime String |
| not_on | != | DateTime String |
| after | \> | DateTime String |
| before | < | DateTime String |
| between_dates | between_dates | Dictionary {“lower”: “lower date”, “upper”:”upper_date”} |

Filters are valid for all [**User Data Attributes**](#c4fd6ad9-4b34-49b6-a5aa-cf1229c2f5c2), [**Session Data Attributes**](#84489c09-8105-44d7-9c2c-b63ef2e824d5) and [**Event Data Attributes**](#be736916-ea99-47b7-9583-fad16e2f6287) having attribute data type (**string**, **integer**, **bool**, **Json**, and **DateTime**)

In case of Attribute data type JSON filters need to be passed in the given format below. There are two data attributes having JSON type [**user_custom_property**](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000968992-Send-User-Properties) and [**event_custom_property**](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000969072-Send-Events-and-Properties)

```
filters=[{"attribute":"user_custom_property","operator":"","property_name":"","value":""}]
filters=[{"attribute":"event_custom_property","operator":"","property_name":"","value":""}]

```

item.description:
_**For analytics endpoints only**_

Grouping is a method of organizing data attributes into groups and then displaying the distribution of those attributes or properties within the groups for a specific aggregation. Each individual group contains two keys: **attribute**, & **max_group_number**(**optional**) in the list of dictionaries.

**max_group_number**: If we group data based on an attribute, it may result in a large amount of grouped data. To restrict this, we can use max_group_number. For instance, if we group data by country and obtain 190 grouped values with their corresponding counts in the response, we can limit the number of countries to the top 10 or top 20 using max_group_number. The remaining values are grouped under "others"

Groupings are valid for all [**User Data Attributes**](#c4fd6ad9-4b34-49b6-a5aa-cf1229c2f5c2), [**Session Data Attributes**](#84489c09-8105-44d7-9c2c-b63ef2e824d5) and [**Event Data Attributes**](#be736916-ea99-47b7-9583-fad16e2f6287) having attribute data type (**string**, **bool**, **and** **DateTime** **String**)

```
Single grouping:
group_by=[{"attribute":""}]
group_by=[{"attribute":"","max_group_number":500}]
Two groupings:
group_by=[{"attribute":"","max_group_number":500},{"attribute":"","max_group_number":500}]

```

_**Note: At most two groupings can be allowed at once on request.**_

In the case of the Attribute data type JSON, this needs to be provided in the given format below. There are two data attributes having JSON type [**user_custom_property**](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000968992-Send-User-Properties) and [**event_custom_property**](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000969072-Send-Events-and-Properties)

```
group_by=[{"attribute":"user_custom_property","property_name":""}]
group_by=[{"attribute":"event_custom_property","property_name":""}]

```

item.description:
_**For analytics endpoints only**_

Aggregation is a process of combining one or more data attributes. The output of an aggregation function is a numerical value that can be used to create a statistical chart. Each individual aggregation contains two keys: **attribute** and **operator** in the list of dictionaries.

Aggregations are valid for all [**User Data Attributes**](#c4fd6ad9-4b34-49b6-a5aa-cf1229c2f5c2), [**Session Data Attributes**](#84489c09-8105-44d7-9c2c-b63ef2e824d5) and [**Event Data Attributes**](#be736916-ea99-47b7-9583-fad16e2f6287) having attribute data type(**Count**, **Integer** and **bool** only)

```
aggregation=[{"attribute":"Attribute Name","operator":"Operator Name"}]

```

Here are the valid aggregation functions:

| **Aggregation Functions** | **Aggregation Operator Name** | **Valid Attribute Data Type** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Summation | sum | Integer, Bool |
| Average | avg | Integer, Bool |
| Minimum | min | Integer, Bool |
| Maximum | max | Integer, Bool |

Note: For JSON [**event_custom_property**](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000969072-Send-Events-and-Properties) and [**user_custom_property**](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000968992-Send-User-Properties) attribute data type, this supports aggregation functions like(sum/avg/min/max) as well if property_name values contain integer values. If aggregation functions are used with string value then this will return an empty response \[[Example](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user/analytics?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&aggregation=[{"attribute":"user_custom_property","operator":"avg","property_name":"age_group"}]&page=1&page_size=20)\]

Sample for JSON type aggregation:

```
aggregation=[{"attribute":"user_custom_property","property_name":"price","operator":"avg"}]
aggregation=[{"attribute":"event_custom_property","property_name":"duration","operator":"avg"}]

```

response.name: Compare event metrics from past month

item.description:
_**(Optional)**_

_**For analytics endpoints only**_

In the case of the comparison parameter, if it’s set to true, the response will include a percentage change compared to the previous date. The previous date is a specific time period before the selected range.

For example, if the current date range is set to one month, the previous date will be the preceding month.

```
comparison=1

```

Note: This parameter is only applicable to the analytics endpoint and cannot be used in conjunction with grouping parameters. If both grouping and comparison are used, the comparison parameter will not function.

The UXCam Data Access APIs are designed using REST principles, featuring predictable URLs with a resource-oriented structure, that accepts requests in form-encoded format, and returns responses in JSON format while adhering to standard HTTP response codes, authentication methods, and verbs. ## Error Handling and Messages UXCam server issues a **status code** for every request made by its clients. The status of the response can be decoded using the table below. | **Status** **Code** | **Reason** | **Description** | | --- | --- | --- | | 200 | OK | The HTTP 200 OK success status response code indicates that the request has succeeded | | 400 | Bad requests | This response status code indicates that the server cannot or will not process the request due to something that is perceived to be a client error (for example, malformed request syntax, invalid request message framing, or deceptive request routing) | | 401 | Unauthorized requests | This response status code indicates that the client request has not been completed because it lacks valid authentication credentials for the requested resource.
Missing valid API Key or APP ID key | | 403 | Forbidden requests | This response status code indicates that the server understands the request but refuses to authorize it. | | 404 | Resource Not Found | The requested resource doesn't exist in the server | | 429 | Request limit exceeded | This response status code indicates the user has sent too many requests in a given amount of time | | 500, 502, 503, 504 | Internal Server Error | These are server error response codes that indicate the server encountered an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request. | ## Query Parameters UXCam Data Access session APIs accept the following request parameters on each and every endpoint: _**Note: Please do not use whitespace in request query parameters.**_ - [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c) - [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4) - [group_by (for analytics endpoints only)](#e962655b-c340-4b03-a585-a1786450d8ca) - [aggregation (for analytics endpoints only)](#b6fb9729-d7e5-43c6-9af5-0a383580b780) - [comparison (for analytics endpoints only) (optional)](#30b06de3-ec97-441a-b934-d0a0cbd8837e)

item.name: Users
User Data Attributes
item.description:
For UXCam Data Access user APIs, all valid attributes that can be used for performing operations such as aggregations, filterings, and groupings based on their data type are listed in the table below. **Users Attribute Table** | **Attribute Category** | **Attribute Name** | **Attribute Data Type** | **Description** | | --- | --- | --- | --- | | DateTime | date_range | DateTime | DateTime when the user used the app | | DateTime | user_first_seen_on | DateTime | DateTime when the user used the app first | | Device | app_version | String | App version on the device when the user was sent | | Device | device_class | String | The class of the device is given by the device size. | | Device | device_id | String | Device Ids are randomly generated unique ids for user devices. For more detail \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004103112-UXCam-and-GDPR-Compliance)\] | | Device | device_manufacturer | String | Device manufacturers recorded within a given user. E.g. Samsung and motorola. | | Device | device_model | String | Device name | | Device | device_os_version | String | Device OS version recorded within a given user. | | Device | device_platform | String | Platform (iOS or Android) of the user
The Value is set to 1 for android users having a device OS as an ANDROID platform
And the value is set to 2 for iOS users having a device OS is an iOS platform | | Device | sdk_version | String | UXCam SDK version on device | | Engagement | user_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of gestures by the user | | Engagement | user_rage_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of rage gestures by the user | | Engagement | user_responsive_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of responsive gestures by the user | | Engagement | user_screen_count | Integer | Total number of screens visited by the user | | Engagement | user_session_duration | Integer | Total time spent in seconds by the user | | Engagement | user_unresponsive_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of unresponsive gestures by the user | | Engagement | event_name | String | Events triggered by users on sessions | | Engagement | session_screen_list | List | List of screens visited by the user | | Session Property | session_uploaded_month | DateTime String | Distribution of users by month (applicable to grouping parameters only) | | Session Property | session_uploaded_week | DateTime String | Distribution of users by week (applicable to grouping parameters only) | | Session Property | session_uploadedon_day | DateTime String | Distribution of users by day (applicable to grouping parameters only) | | User | device_city | String | Country city based on device IP address | | User | device_country | String | Country name based on device IP address | | User | user_name | String | Randomly assigned alias for users. Note: This is not the real user name, alias, or ID. For more detail \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004103112-UXCam-and-GDPR-Compliance)\] | | User | uxcamuserid | String | UXCam User ID of the user | | User | user_custom_property | JSON | Additional properties attach for users on sending sessions |

item.description:
A user list provides qualitative data, including details about the device, user interactions, personalized user properties, and location data.

### Request Parameters

Now that you have explored the data attributes and query parameters, This list user endpoint supports the following query parameters as given in the URL structure below.

- [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c)
- [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4)
    

For more information on parameters see the [Query parameters](#0af0fa88-746b-409f-8f41-a32fc16337f4)

**Structure of API URL:**

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user?appid=appid&apikey=apikey&filters=list of filters&page=page number&page_size=number of data in single request

```

In order to authenticate the list user API, appid and API key are required. See [**Authentication**](#6930510a-ccfb-426d-8cbe-21fc30b4a9b2) for more details.

### Response Structure

Now that you have explored the data attributes and query parameters, let's take a look at the response you will receive for a specific API request. The response is in JSON format and includes a data array with multiple objects enclosed in curly brackets. Each object can be thought of as a new row and is separated by a comma. Each object includes several properties, which are represented as key-value pairs.

The List user API provides information about a user in several key-value pairs grouped under different keys: user custom properties are under the "**property**" key, user device information is under the "**device**" key, user engagement metrics are under the "**usage**" key, and user location information is under the "**location**" key.

item.description:
This endpoint for analyzing user data offers aggregated numerical data that can be utilized to create statistical graphs and gain valuable insights.

### Request Parameters

Now that you have explored the data attributes and query parameters, This user analytics endpoint supports the following query parameters as given in the URL structure below.

- [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c)
- [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4)
- [group_by](#e962655b-c340-4b03-a585-a1786450d8ca)
- [aggregation](#b6fb9729-d7e5-43c6-9af5-0a383580b780)
- [comparison](#30b06de3-ec97-441a-b934-d0a0cbd8837e)
    

For more information see: [**Query parameters**](#0af0fa88-746b-409f-8f41-a32fc16337f4) section

**Structure of API URL:**

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user/analytics?appid=appid&apikey=apikey&filters=list of filter&aggregation=list of aggregation&group_by=list of groupings>&page=page number&page_size=number of data in single request

```

In order to authenticate the user analytics API, appid and API key are required. See [**Authentication**](#6930510a-ccfb-426d-8cbe-21fc30b4a9b2) for more details.

### Response Structure

The user analytics API provides aggregated data of users based on the user’s query which is grouped by grouping attributes. It gives us all of the user aggregate data in the output so it can be used to plot statistical charts.

An entity that engages with an application is referred to as a user. A user can be specifically linked to a device by their device ID. If a singular user has multiple devices, the user can be tracked across all devices by utilizing API calls.

## User Endpoints

UXCAM Data Access API provides **two** endpoint URLs for retrieving both qualitative **(List User)** and quantitative **(Analyze User)** data for users. The endpoint URLs are as follows:

List User: [https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user)

Analyze User: [https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user/analytics](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user/analytics)

item.name: Sessions
Session Data Attributes
item.description:
For UXCam Data Access session APIs, all valid attributes that can be used for performing operations such as aggregations, filterings, and groupings based on their data type are listed in the table below. **Sessions Attribute Table** | **Attribute Category** | **Attribute Name** | **Attribute Data Type** | **Description** | | --- | --- | --- | --- | | DateTime | date_range | DateTime | DateTime when the user used the app and sessions are uploaded | | Device | app_version | String | Device app version recorded within a given session. | | Device | device_class | String | Class of the device given by the device size. | | Device | device_id | String | Device Ids are randomly generated unique ids for user devices. For more detail \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004103112-UXCam-and-GDPR-Compliance)\] | | Device | device_manufacturer | String | Device manufacturers recorded within a given session. E.g. Samsung and motorola. | | Device | device_model | String | Device name | | Device | device_os_version | String | Device operating system version | | Device | device_platform | String | Platform (iOS or Android) of the user
The Value is set to 1 for android users having a device OS as an ANDROID platform
And the value is set to 2 for iOS users having a device OS is an iOS platform | | Session Property | event_name | String | List of events that occurred during the session | | Session Property | sdk_version | String | UXCam SDK version on device | | Session Property | session_crashed | Bool String | Show only sessions that are crashed / not crashed
The value set to true for crashed sessions and false for not crashed sessions | | Session Property | session_duration | Integer | Total session length in seconds | | Session Property | session_gesture_count | Integer | Total gesture on the individual session | | Session Property | session_has_video | Bool String (true/false) | Is there a video for the session?
Value is set to true and false for sessions with no video | | Session Property | session_new_users_count | Count | Total new users | | Session Property | session_number_of_user | Integer | Count of sessions for the particular user. | | Session Property | session_rage_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of rage gestures on the session | | Session Property | session_responsive_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of responsive gestures on the session | | Session Property | session_screen_count | Integer | Total number of screens visited on the session | | Session Property | session_screen_list | list | List of screens visited during the session | | Session Property | session_unique_screen_count | Integer | Total number of screen visited on the session | | Session Property | session_unique_user_count | Count | Total users | | Session Property | session_unresponsive_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of unresponsive gestures on the session | | Session Property | session_uploaded_month | DateTime String | Distribution of sessions by month (relevant to grouping parameter only) | | Session Property | session_uploaded_week | DateTime String | Distribution of sessions by week(Mon-Sun) (relevant to grouping parameter only) | | Session Property | session_uploadedon_day | DateTime String | Distribution of sessions by days (relevant to grouping parameter only) | | Session Property | session_id | String | UXCam Session ID of user | | User | device_city | String | Country city name based on device IP address.For more details on IP Address \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360025475671-Discard-IP-Address)\] | | User | device_country | String | Country name based on device IP address | | User | uxcamuserid | String | UXCam User ID of user | | User | user_name | String | Randomly assigned alias for users. Note: This is not the real user name, alias, or ID. For more detail \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004103112-UXCam-and-GDPR-Compliance)\] | | User | user_custom_property | JSON | Additional custom properties attached to sessions |

item.description:
A session list provides qualitative data, including details about the device, interactions of user within session, personalized user properties, and location data.

### Request Parameters

This list session endpoint supports the following query parameters apart from authentication as given in the URL structure below.

- [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c)
- [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4)
    

For more information see: [**Query parameters**](#0af0fa88-746b-409f-8f41-a32fc16337f4) section

Structure of API URL:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session?appid=appid&apikey=apikey&filters=list of filters&page=page number&page_size=number of data in single request

```

In order to authenticate the list sessions API, appid and API key are required. See [**Authentication**](#6930510a-ccfb-426d-8cbe-21fc30b4a9b2) for more details.

### Response Structure

The List session API provides information about sessions in several key-value pairs grouped under different keys: session properties are under the "**property**" key, device information is under the "**device**" key, user properties are under the "**user**" key, and device location information is under the "**location**" key.

Here in the response, their **video** key contains the session video link and this link has an expiry date of **one week**.

item.description:
This endpoint for analyzing session data offers aggregated numerical data that can be utilized to create statistical graphs and gain valuable insights.

### Request Parameters

This session analytics endpoint supports the following query parameters as given in the URL structure below.

- [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c)
- [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4)
- [group_by](#e962655b-c340-4b03-a585-a1786450d8ca)
- [aggregation](#b6fb9729-d7e5-43c6-9af5-0a383580b780)
- [comparison](#30b06de3-ec97-441a-b934-d0a0cbd8837e)
    

For more information see: [**Query parameters**](#0af0fa88-746b-409f-8f41-a32fc16337f4) section

Structure of API URL:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session/analytics?appid=appid&apikey=apikey&filters=list of filter&aggregation=list of aggregation&group_by=list of groupings>&page=page number&page_size=number of data in single request

```

In order to authenticate the session analytics API, appid and API key are required. See [**Authentication**](#6930510a-ccfb-426d-8cbe-21fc30b4a9b2) for more details.

### Response Structure

The session analytics API provides aggregated data of sessions based on the session query which is grouped by grouping attributes. It gives us all of the session aggregate data in the output so it can be used to plot statistical charts.

A session refers to a series of actions and interactions that a user carries out while using an application, within a specific period of time. A session begins when a user launches an application and ends when they exit or become inactive. Data collected during this period is referred to as session data. ## Session Endpoints UXCAM provides **two** endpoint URLs for retrieving both qualitative**(Session List)** and quantitative **(Session Analytics)** data for sessions. The endpoint URLs are as follows: Session List: [https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session) Session Analytics: [https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session/analytics](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session/analytics) ## API Update Prior to February 1st, 2024, the **video key** contained the session video link. However, from now on the **video key** will be present but by default this value will be null and will not include the session video link. If you need the video link in the response, you will need to use a Flag with_video=true , to include it. This video link will still have an expiry date of **one week.** Please refer to the example below. **Example:** ``` http://api.uxcam.com/v2/session?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&with_video=true ``` **Response with flag with_video**[=](http://api.uxcam.com/v2/session?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&with_video=true)**true** ``` json { "sessionId": "60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96", "video": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/upload.uxcam.com/5fa4e6fce6bc8617563668bf/60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb/60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96/video.mp4?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIA4BSZZTEWCXZ3ZP6T&Expires=1706095540&Signature=NruRZtmMfDtBXushOPWXDplIXOY=", "url": "https://app.uxcam.com/app/60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb/sessions/list/1/60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96", "sessionNumber": 20 } ``` **Response with flag with_video**[=](http://api.uxcam.com/v2/session?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&with_video=true)**false or without flag** ``` json { "sessionId": "60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96", "video": null, "url": "https://app.uxcam.com/app/60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb/sessions/list/1/60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96", "sessionNumber": 20 } ``` The List session API provides information about sessions in several key-value pairs grouped under different keys: session properties are under the “_**property**_” key, device information is under the “_**device**_” key, user properties are under the “_**user**_” key, and device location information is under the “_**location**_” key.Here in the response, the **video** key is present by default with a value of null. Here in the response, the **video** key is present by default with a value of null. ``` json { "success": true, "data": [ { "sessionId": "60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96", "video": "null", "sessionNumber": 20, # nth number of session "url": "https://app.uxcam.com/app/60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb/sessions/list/1/60f7dd4efd9c2f001169bb96", "property": { "uploadedServerTime": "2023-01-16 10:43:47", "deviceLocalDateTime": "2021-09-10 10:43:47", "verifiedServerTime": "2021-07-21 08:39:42", "offlineRecorded": false, "hasVideo": false, "isCrashed": false, "durationSec": 55.009, "totalGesture": 26, "totalScreen": 17, "uniqueScreens:[ "First activity", "HomeActivity-update", "SubCategoryActivity_updated", "ItemListActivityTest", "Cart Activity" ], "uniqueScreensCount": 5, "rageGestureCount": 0, "networkType": "wifi" }, "user": { "kUXCam_UserIdentity": "U#5066", "gender": "male", "exp_var_key": "test_2", "age_group": "10-19", "alias": "Isaias Altenwerth", "language": "English", "loyalty_card": "no", "acqn_source": "none", "uxcamuserid": "60f7dd46972a633e88696d6b" }, "device": { "carrierCode": "42901", "carrierName": "Verizon Wireless", "osName": " O_MR1", "appVersion": "1.5", "sdkVersion": "3.3.5", "osVersion": "8.1", "language": "English", "country": "USA", "totalStorageInKB": 11289, "totalRamInKB": 2815, "freeRamInKb": null, "dpi": -1, "height": 2340, "width": 1080, "type": "Phone", "class": "Android Large", "producer": "Huawei", "model": "JKM-LX1", "deviceId": "03c1e123941a19ec", "isNotificationEnabled": null, "isRooted": false, "platform": "android" }, "location": { "countryCode": "US", "city": "Albany", "longitude": -73.7987, "latitude": 42.6664 } } ] } ```

item.name: Events
Event Data Attributes
item.description:
For UXCam Data Access event APIs, all valid attributes that can be used for performing operations such as aggregations, filterings, and groupings based on their data type are listed in the table below. **Events Attribute Table** | Attribute Category | Attribute Name | Attribute Data Type | Description | | --- | --- | --- | --- | | DateTime | date_range | DateTime | DateTime when the user used the app and sessions/events are uploaded | | Device | app_version | String | Device app version recorded within a given session. | | Device | device_class | String | Class of the device given by the device size. | | Device | device_id | String | Device Ids are randomly generated unique ids for user devices. For more detail \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004103112-UXCam-and-GDPR-Compliance)\] | | Device | device_manufacturer | String | Device manufacturers recorded within a given session. E.g. Samsung and motorola. | | Device | device_model | String | Device name | | Device | device_os_version | String | Device operating system version | | Device | device_platform | String | Platform (iOS or Android) of the user
The Value is set to 1 for android users having a device OS as an ANDROID platform
And the value is set to 2 for iOS users having a device OS is an iOS platform | | Session Property | sdk_version | String | UXCam SDK version on device | | Session Property | session_crashed | Bool String | Show only sessions that are crashed / not crashed
The value set to true for crashed sessions and false for not crashed sessions | | Session Property | session_duration | Integer | Total session length in seconds | | Session Property | session_gesture_count | Integer | Total gesture on the individual session | | Session Property | session_has_video | Bool String (true/false) | Is there a video for the session?
Value is set to true and false for sessions with no video
| | Session Property | session_new_users_count | Count | Total new users | | Session Property | session_number_of_user | Integer | count of sessions for the particular user. View user 10th session with UXCamuserid | | Session Property | session_rage_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of rage gestures on the session | | Session Property | session_responsive_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of responsive gestures on the session | | Session Property | session_screen_count | Integer | Total number of screens visited on the session | | Session Property | session_screen_list | list | List of screens visited during the session | | Session Property | session_unique_screen_count | Integer | Total number of screen visited on the session | | Session Property | session_unresponsive_gesture_count | Integer | Total number of unresponsive gestures on the session | | Event | event_uploaded_month | DateTime String | Distribution of events by month (relevant to grouping parameter only) | | Event | event_uploaded_week | DateTime String | Distribution of events by week(Mon-Sun) (relevant to grouping parameter only) | | Event | event_uploadedon_day | DateTime String | Distribution of events by days (relevant to grouping parameter only) | | User | device_city | String | Country city name based on device IP address.For more details on IP Address \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360025475671-Discard-IP-Address)\] | | User | device_country | String | Country name based on device IP address | | User | uxcamuserid | String | UXCam User ID of user | | User | user_name | String | Randomly assigned alias for users. Note: This is not the real user name, alias, or ID. For more detail \[[Link](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004103112-UXCam-and-GDPR-Compliance)\] | | User | user_custom_property | JSON | Additional custom properties attached to sessions | | Event | event_name | String | Event triggered by users on sessions | | Event | event_screen_name | String | Screen name on which event happened | | Event | event_custom_property | JSON | Additional properties attach for events on sessions |

item.description:
A event list provides qualitative data, including details about the device, interactions of user within session, personalized user properties, and location data.

### Request Parameters

This list events endpoint supports the following query parameters apart from authentication as given in the URL structure below.

- [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c)
- [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4)
    

For more information see: [**Query parameters**](#0af0fa88-746b-409f-8f41-a32fc16337f4) section

Structure of API URL:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/event?appid=appid&apikey=apikey&filters=list of filters&page=page number&page_size=number of data in single request

```

In order to authenticate the list event API, appid and API key are required. See [**Authentication**](#6930510a-ccfb-426d-8cbe-21fc30b4a9b2) for more details.

### Response Structure

The List event API provides information about events in several key-value pairs grouped under different keys: session properties data are under the "**sessionProperty**" key, device information is under the "**device**" key, user properties are under the "**userProperty**" key, and event custom properties information is under the "**eventProperty**" key.

item.description:
This endpoint for analyzing event data offers aggregated numerical data that can be utilized to create statistical graphs and gain valuable insights.

### Request Parameters

This event analytics endpoint supports the following query parameters as given in the URL structure below.

- [pagination](#35217af0-544f-4b1e-8192-525a1503614c)
- [filters](#0944c462-0b2e-469e-8625-c5920032fed4)
- [group_by](#e962655b-c340-4b03-a585-a1786450d8ca)
- [aggregation](#b6fb9729-d7e5-43c6-9af5-0a383580b780)
- [comparison](#30b06de3-ec97-441a-b934-d0a0cbd8837e)
    

For more information see: [**Query parameters**](#0af0fa88-746b-409f-8f41-a32fc16337f4) section

Structure of API URL:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session/analytics?appid=appid&apikey=apikey&filters=list of filter&aggregation=list of aggregation&group_by=list of groupings>&page=page number&page_size=number of data in single request

```

In order to authenticate the event analytics API, appid and API key are required. See [**Authentication**](#6930510a-ccfb-426d-8cbe-21fc30b4a9b2) for more details.

### Response Structure

The event analytics API provides aggregated data of sessions based on the event query which is grouped by grouping attributes. It gives us all of the session aggregate data in the output so it can be used to plot statistical charts.

When a user takes an action or something happens within an app, it generates event data. This data can be sorted and organized according to the characteristics listed in the table. Additionally, every instance of event data can be classified based on all session attributes.

When a user performs an action or some actions are triggered within an app, it generates event data. This data can be sorted and organized according to the characteristics listed in the table. Additionally, every instance of event data can be classified based on all session attributes.

  
For example, when a user taps the login button in the app, it is considered a tap gesture (automatically captured). Additionally, SDK developers can send events and events' properties to UXCam to gather more insights about the users' behavior. For more detail [check here](https://help.uxcam.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000969072-Send-Events-and-Properties).

### Event Endpoints

UXCAM provides two endpoint URLs for retrieving both qualitative **(Event List)** and quantitative **(Event Analytics)** data for events. The endpoint URLs are as follows:

Event List: [https://api.uxcam.com/v2/event](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user)

Event Analytics: [https://api.uxcam.com/v2/event/analytics](https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user/analytics)

item.name: Browser
item.description:
You can make the API request directly on the URL bar on the browser, after the successful request you will receive the response on the browser itself. The response is presented in raw JSON format. You can format the response using a JSON formatting extension for your browser. Some of the options are JSON Formatter, JSONView, etc for Chrome, and JSON Peep for Safari. You can easily find an applicable one for your browser.

Similarly, if you intend to perform further analysis you can write scripts to request the data and then process the response as per your need.

**Example:**

Session List:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/session?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&page=1&page_size=5

```

Event List:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/event?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&filters=[{"attribute":"device_platform","operator":"equal","value":"1"}]

```

User Analytics:

```
https://api.uxcam.com/v2/user/analytics?appid=60f6c0b8b97ba419120b82eb&apikey=9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618&filters=[{"attribute":"date_range","operator":"between_dates","value":{"lower":"2023-04-02T00:00:00Z","upper":"2023-05-02T23:59:59Z"}}]&group_by=[{"attribute": "device_country","max_group_number":5}]

```

``` python
import requests
import json
headers = {
  'apikey': '9c633412-927a-4f4e-87bc-386dc1e3a618',
}

params = {

  'page': 1,
  'page_size': 50,
   'filters': json.dumps([{"attribute": "date_range",
                         "operator": "between_dates",
                         "value": {
                             "lower": "2023-04-02T00:00:00Z",
                             "upper": "2023-05-02T23:59:59Z"
                         }}]),
   'group_by': json.dumps([{"attribute": "sdk_version",
                          "max_group_number": 3}])
}
response = requests.get(url=URL, params=params, headers=headers)
json_response = response.json()
print(json_response)

```

item.name: Future Plans
item.description:
This document outlines the plan for the upcoming feature release of Public Data Access API for **three** more APIs: **Screens**, **Gestures** along with **Issues.** Additionally, several existing features will be improved and enhanced. The purpose of this document is to provide a clear and comprehensive overview of the new features and improvements that will be made available to our users.

This feature release represents a significant step forward for UXCam Data Access V2 APIs. With the new features and improvements, users will have an even better experience using our product.
